    <main id="conteudo"><section class="page-hero"><div class="wrap"><p class="eyebrow"><span class="signal"></span>Privacy</p><h1>Privacy Policy</h1><p>How VeVolt uses information and permissions to help electric-car drivers.</p></div></section><section class="section"><div class="wrap legal">
          <p>
            VeVolt helps electric-car drivers find charging locations, plan routes,
            track savings and organize charging. The app does not require an email
            and password account. Optional features such as VeVolt Community,
            Premium, Market and VeVolt Condo use the backend only for the purposes
            described in this policy.
          </p>

          <h2>1. Data handled by this version</h2>
          <p>The app may store locally on the device:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>vehicle type, brand, model and year;</li>
            <li>average range, battery capacity, connector and current battery level;</li>
            <li>initial setup, saved locations and followed chargers;</li>
            <li>reservations and charging sessions recorded on the device.</li>
          </ul>
          <p>
            This data supports app screens and local range, route, cost and savings
            estimates. Data voluntarily submitted to VeVolt Community or VeVolt
            Condo may be sent to the backend to provide those shared features.
          </p>

          <h2>2. Maps, location and external services</h2>
          <p>
            Personal vehicle data, saved locations, device location and local
            charging history are not sent to the VeVolt backend.
          </p>
          <p>
            The map uses MapLibre and OpenFreeMap with OpenStreetMap data. As with
            any internet request, the provider may receive technical information
            needed to deliver map tiles, such as the IP address and displayed map
            region.
          </p>
          <p>
            When location access is allowed, approximate latitude and longitude may
            be sent to Open Charge Map only to return nearby charging locations.
            VeVolt does not collect background location.
          </p>
          <p>
            In VeVolt Market, country, postal code and language are sent over HTTPS
            to the backend only when the user starts a search. The service may use
            BrasilAPI in Brazil, Nominatim/OpenStreetMap elsewhere and
            Zippopotam.us as a fallback. Results may remain in volatile cache for up
            to 24 hours without durable storage of the postal code or coordinates.
          </p>

          <h2>3. Premium and Google Play</h2>
          <p>
            Premium purchases and subscriptions are processed exclusively by
            Google Play under the user's Google account settings and Google Play
            policies.
          </p>
          <p>
            Premium validation sends the purchase token, product and a random
            installation identifier over HTTPS. The backend queries the Google Play
            Developer API and stores only SHA-256 hashes, status, expiry, test flag
            and verification dates. Vehicle data, location and charging history are
            not sent for this purpose.
          </p>

          <h2>4. VeVolt Community</h2>
          <p>
            When users contribute, the app sends the charger's public identifier and
            metadata, condition, price, rating, comment and optional photo. The
            installation identifier is stored only as a hash and creates an
            anonymous pseudonym.
          </p>
          <p>
            Photos are resized and re-encoded on the device to strip metadata. They
            remain in private Google Cloud storage and are delivered by the VeVolt
            API. Publications can be reported, moderated, blocked locally and
            deleted by their author together with the photo. Maximum retention is
            two years.
          </p>
          <p>
            Followed chargers remain on the device. Alerts check the API without
            collecting background location. Community reports are user
            contributions and are not operator confirmations.
          </p>

          <h2>5. VeVolt Condo</h2>
          <p>
            VeVolt Condo sends the entered name, condominium, unit, country,
            currency, shared chargers, reservations and charging sessions,
            including energy and cost when recorded.
          </p>
          <p>
            Access does not use email or password. The app stores a random token in
            Android private storage and the server stores only its hash. Invite
            codes are single-use and expire.
          </p>

          <h2>6. Storage and security</h2>
          <p>
            Local data uses Android DataStore in the app's private storage.
            Automatic backup and extraction are disabled, unencrypted traffic is
            blocked, and map, charger, geocoding, VeVolt backend and Google Play
            connections use HTTPS. QR code processing takes place on the device.
          </p>
          <p>
            No storage or transmission method is completely risk-free. Keep the app
            updated and protect access to your device.
          </p>

          <h2>7. Permissions and sensitive features</h2>
          <p>
            Location and camera permissions are optional. Location finds nearby
            chargers. The camera processes QR codes on the device with ML Kit
            Barcode Scanning and does not send camera images to VeVolt servers.
            Notifications may be requested when a user follows a charger. The app
            does not request contacts, microphone or broad external-storage access.
          </p>

          <h2>8. Retention and deletion</h2>
          <p>
            Local data remains until deleted from Profile, Android settings or by
            uninstalling the app. Premium entitlement records expire 90 days after
            subscription expiry, and RTDN identifiers expire after 30 days. Deleting
            Profile data also attempts to remove the linked Premium record.
          </p>
          <p>
            A VeVolt Condo member can leave and delete their association and
            records. A sole administrator can delete the whole condominium; when
            other members remain, the administrator must arrange closure first.
          </p>

          <h2>9. Website tester registration</h2>
          <p>
            When someone requests closed-test access, the website records the
            submitted email, page language, date and request status. This data is
            used only to manage the test and send related messages. To limit abuse,
            the server temporarily stores a technical identifier derived from the
            IP address without retaining the address in plain text. The email is not
            sold or used for advertising.
          </p>

          <h2>10. Children</h2>
          <p>VeVolt is not directed to children.</p>

          <h2>11. Policy changes</h2>
          <p>
            This policy will be updated before introducing email or social login,
            new backend purposes, personal-vehicle synchronization, charging
            payments, analytics or additional data sharing. The update date will
            change when material revisions are published.
          </p>

          <h2>12. Contact</h2>
          <p>
            Privacy questions and deletion requests can be sent to
            <a href="mailto:devs@pascoal.eti.br">devs@pascoal.eti.br</a>.
          </p>
